      <aside class="calc-sidebar">
        <div class="card sidebar-card">
          <h2>What is a currency converter?</h2>
          <p>A currency converter calculates the equivalent value of an amount in one currency expressed in another currency, using an exchange rate. Exchange rates fluctuate constantly based on financial markets.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card sidebar-card">
          <h3>Frequently asked questions</h3>
          <details>
            <summary>Are these exchange rates live?</summary>
            <p>No, these are approximate reference rates. For live rates and transactions, always check your bank or a source like the European Central Bank (ECB).</p>
          </details>
          <details>
            <summary>Why does my bank give me a worse rate?</summary>
            <p>Banks and exchange services apply a margin or commission on top of the mid-market rate. This is how they make money on currency exchange.</p>
          </details>
          <details>
            <summary>What is the mid-market rate?</summary>
            <p>The mid-market rate (also called interbank rate) is the midpoint between buy and sell prices. It is the fairest rate but typically not available to retail customers.</p>
          </details>
        </div>
